<body>
  <h1>üì± BabyQuip App Redesign (2024‚Äì2025)</h1>
  <p><strong>Role:</strong> Senior UX Designer  
  <br><strong>Team:</strong> Me (UX), Kim (VP Design), Imani (UX), Dev (Vietnam agency)</p>

  <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Shift the mobile rental experience from <code>provider-first</code> to <code>gear-first</code>, to align with the web experience and improve usability, trust, and conversion.</p>

  <section>
    <h2>Landing + Entry Flow</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Before: Explore tab was default. Users got lost.</li>
      <li>Now: Users land directly into gear-first browsing or enter search modal.</li>
      <li>2 options tested: CTA-first or modal-first ‚Üí both lead into the same trip setup.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Impact:</strong> More sessions begin with trip info. Higher engagement.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Trip Info Input</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Before: Rigid linear form blocked entry if info was missing.</li>
      <li>Now: Progressive disclosure ‚Äî start with address, skip/edit date & time later.</li>
      <li>Supports both planners & last-minute renters.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Reduce bounce on form. More trips started.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Shopping Page</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Before: No top categories, poor scannability.</li>
      <li>Now: Gear-first top nav (icons or images ‚Äî A/B tested).</li>
      <li>No personalization yet ‚Äî focused on clear hierarchy: category ‚Üí items ‚Üí cart.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Reduce time to first item added. Increase add-to-cart rate.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Cart</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>2 clear states: 
        <ul>
          <li>No QP selected ‚Üí CTA to select</li>
          <li>QP selected ‚Üí mini-summary, lighter "Replace QP"</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Support for cancellation policy, quantity edit, and upsells.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Clarify state. Guide toward checkout without confusion.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Select QP (Quality Provider)</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Before: Long list, hard to choose.</li>
      <li>Now: Filter/sort available. Upsells integrated ‚Äî users can add more gear.</li>
      <li>Service fee preview shown upfront.</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Reduce drop-off. Support confident, fast decisions.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Checkout</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Before: Redundant survey, forced password, surprise T&Cs.</li>
      <li>Now:
        <ul>
          <li>Survey removed</li>
          <li>Trust copy cleaned up</li>
          <li>Less steps, fewer form fields</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Goal:</strong> Faster checkout. Fewer abandoned carts.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Notes</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Design was based on existing web model ‚Äî not pure mobile-first.</li>
      <li>Constraints: Small team, no dynamic content, limited dev bandwidth.</li>
      <li>Most decisions focused on reducing friction + aligning cross-platform behavior.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

